panels.description:
The size of the queue of  routing instructions waiting for completion processing is under limit.
When the queue size reaches the limit defined in IXN Node, reading of  routing instructions stops.

targets.expr:
min by (tenant)(
  (ixnnode_instructions_processing_queue_concurrency_limit - 
    sum without(type)(ixnnode_instructions_processing_queue_size))
  +
  increase(ixnnode_all_instructions_received_total[1m])

) > bool 0
OR min by (tenant)((up{servicename="ixn", container="ixn-node"} > 0) > bool 1)

panels.title: Processing of Instructions Received from ORS
ORS Health Check

panels.content:
In order to monitor availability and latency for communications following event flow is implemented between Tenant IXN Node and ORS nodes
0. Each Tenant IXN Node every 15 seconds sends health check request type 'ixn_ping' to ORS Service Nodes using:
 * **Redis** stream 'NewInteractionsStream' with refId, timeStamp, tenantId,  and instructionStreamName 
0. Random ORS Node take request from the Redis stream and send ping instruction back to same IXN Node using Redis instructionStreamName :
 * **Redis** stream <instructionStreamName> with same refId, timeStamp, name,  and RQ Node streamName, 
0. IXN Node communicate back to ORS Node via
 * **RQ Service** stream <streamName> event ixn_ping, with timeStamp
0. ORS node send unsolicited ping to known IXN Node if no ping comes from IXN Node
 * **Redis** stream <instructionStreamName> with refId 0, timeStamp, name,  and RQ Node streamName
panels.title: How IXN <-> ORS Health Check Works

panels.content:
Panel Title Description
IXN Ping Sending via Redis Shows status summary of sending pings process. Green state means IXN Node was able to send all ping messages via both Redis and RQ Service within a specific time range. Red state means the opposite.
ORS Reply Receival Shows quantitive ratio between pings sent via Redis and replies received. States: OK 90 - 100% replied, WARN 60 - 89% replied, ALERT less than 60% replied.
IXN Ping Sending via RQ Service Shows quantitive ratio between pings replied by ORS and then sent via RQ Service. States: OK 90 - 100% sent, WARN 60 - 89% sent, ALERT less than 60% sent.
Pings Sent and Replied via Redis Total Graph shows counters for pings sent via Redis and replies received. For each tenant three types of counters are present: "Sent by tenant", "Replied to tenant by specific ORS node", "Replied to tenant total".
Pings Sent and Replied via Redis Rate Graph shows rate for the same counters as Pings Sent and Replied via Redis Total.
Pings Failed to Send via Redis Total Graph shows counters for pings failed to send via redis.
Pings Failed to Send via Redis Rate Graph shows rate for the same counters as Pings Failed to Send via Redis Total.
Pings Sent via RQ Service Total Graph shows counters for pings sent via RQ Service separately For each ORS node.
Pings Sent via RQ Service Rate Graph shows rate for the same counters as Pings Sent via RQ Service Total.
Pings Failed to Send via RQ Service Total Graph shows counters for pings failed to send via RQ Service.
Pings Failed to Send via RQ Service Rate Graph shows rate for the same counters as Pings Failed to Send via RQ Service Total.
Roundtrip Duration for Pings Sent via Redis Graphs show information about time duration between sending a ping and receiving a reply. Two types of graphs are displayed for each tenant and each ORS node:
Roundtrip Duration for Time Range - histogram shows distribution between buckets for the selected time range.
Roundtrip Duration over Time - heatmap shows distribution between buckets over time. The more bright color the more pings in a bucket within a specific time span.
One-way Duration for Pings Sent via Redis Graphs show information about time duration between a ping (reply or unsolicited one) being sent by ORS and received by IXN Service. The information is based on local sending time passed in a message by ORS, so time difference between clocks may have a significant impact on this metric.
There are same types of graphs as for Roundtrip Duration for Pings Sent via Redis
panels.title: Panels Description

panels.description: Status of sending health check messages via redis and RqNode
panels.title: IXN Ping Sending via Redis

panels.description: Matching between messages sent and replied via Redis.

targets.expr:
min by (tenant)(clamp_max(floor(
  sum without (ors_node)(increase(ixnnode_ors_health_check_replied_total[5m])) / 
    increase(ixnnode_ors_health_check_sent_total[5m]) 
  * 10
), 10))
OR min by (tenant)((up{servicename="ixn", container="ixn-node"} > 0) > bool 1)

panels.title: ORS Reply Receival

panels.description: Status of sending health check messages via RQ Service. It is based on matching number of pings received from ORS (as replies or unsolicited ones) and sent via RQ Service within some time interval.

targets.expr:
((min by (tenant)(clamp_max(floor(
  sum without (ors_node)(increase(ixnnode_ors_health_check_rqnode_sent_total[3m])) / 
    sum without (ors_node)(increase(ixnnode_ors_health_check_replied_total[3m])) * 10
), 10)) < bool 6)
+
(min by (tenant)(clamp_max(floor(
  sum without (ors_node)(increase(ixnnode_ors_health_check_rqnode_sent_total[3m])) / 
    sum without (ors_node)(increase(ixnnode_ors_health_check_replied_total[3m])) * 10
), 10)) < bool 9)
+
(min by (tenant)(clamp_max(floor(
  sum without (ors_node)(increase(ixnnode_ors_health_check_rqnode_sent_total[3m])) / 
    sum without (ors_node)(increase(ixnnode_ors_health_check_replied_total[3m])) * 10
), 10)) <= bool 10)) > 0
OR min by (tenant)(((up{servicename="ixn", container="ixn-node"} > 0) > bool 1) + 3)

panels.description:
Time duration between a health check message was sent and replied.
This panel shows distribution between buckets for the selected time range.
Unit: seconds.
"1" bucket was excluded due to the bug in Grafana. It should be put back after upgrading to 7.X.

targets.expr:
sum without (instance)(increase(ixnnode_ors_health_check_roundtrip_duration_sec_bucket{tenant=~"$Tenant",ors_node=~"$ORS",le!="1"}[${__range_s}s]))
/ ignoring (le) group_left
sum without (instance)(increase(ixnnode_ors_health_check_roundtrip_duration_sec_bucket{tenant=~"$Tenant",ors_node=~"$ORS",le="+Inf"}[${__range_s}s]))
